view.description: Data set from My Neighborhood Map program.

columns.name: City Feature
columns.description: Type of City of Seattle feature, such as traffic cameras, parks, playfields, Neighborhood Service Centers, etc.

columns.name: Common Name
columns.description: This is the commonly referred name of the feature. It may be a name of a building, a park, or a location

columns.name: Address
columns.description: Address is the most specific location information for a feature. It ranges from a building on a campus (like Cunningham Hall on the University of Washington campus, to an intersection, to a specific street address.

top.item: Aurora Ave. N and N 59th St.

columns.name: Website
columns.description: This is the most recent known correct website address for the given feature.

columns.name: Longitude
columns.description: This is the longitude value. Lines of longitude run perpendicular to lines of latitude, and all pass through both poles.

columns.name: Latitude
columns.description: This is the latitude value. Lines of latitude are parallel to the equator.
